<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-34-1279 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper outlines the geothermal energy resources of Canada and theirpotential as an energy alternative. The geologic principles of geothermalenergy are also discussed. Areas having potentially exploitable geothermalresources are the east coast and western plains (for low temperatureheat) and the western mountains, where high-temperature heat sourcesexist. 3 figs.</TEXT></DOC>